article.headline: New Mexico State 74, South Alabama 65
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. (AP) -- James Moore scored 20 points and Duane John added 16 to lead New Mexico State to a 74-65 victory over South Alabama on Saturday night. Moore hit 7-of-17 from the field and all six of his free throws for the Aggies (11-11, 5-6 Sun Belt Conference). John hit 3-of-5 from 3-point range and made 5-of-6 free throws. Allen Haynes also reached double figures for New Mexico State with 11 points. Henry Williams led the Jaguars (9-14, 3-8) with 18 points and a game-high 12 rebounds, while Shane Spencer added 11 points. The Jaguars hit 52 percent of their shots in the opening half, building up a 33-31 halftime lead, but the Aggies outscored South Alabama 43-32 in the second half. New Mexico State also outrebounded the Jaguars 38-30.
